news.title: Jaipur civic body attaches five properties over non-payment of UD tax
news.para: JMC-Heritage administration attached four properties in Hawa Mahal zone on Friday after the property owners did not respond to notices regarding timely payment of UD tax.

news.title: MNCs implement green building norms in New town and Sector V in Kolkata
news.para: According to the Indian Green Building Council (IGBC), meeting global green standards by reducing carbon footprint and using renewable energy has become mandatory for Indian MNCs to strike deals with their foreign counterparts.

news.title: RWAs of Secunderabad cantonment oppose new groundwater usage norms
news.para: “There is no provision in the draft to enable us to apply for a certificate of non-availability of adequate drinking water from SCB. This clause must be included in the draft,” a resident said.

news.title: Luxury & sustainable real estate takes center stage at The Economic Times Real Estate Conclave & Awards 2024
news.para: The Economic Times Real Estate Conclave & Awards 2024 held in Taj Santacruz, Mumbai on February 23, 2024 witnesses gathering of top real estate stakeholders sharing their views on some of the pertinent issues of the Indian real estate sector.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP razes eight illegal colonies on 12 acres
news.para: Four unauthorised colonies, carved out on permit line in the revenue estate of Bhondsi village — wherein 24 under-construction structures, 10 boundary walls, one aluminium gate factory and 600m of road network — were demolished.

news.title: PMC Bank case: ED attaches shops worth over Rs 13 crore in Pune mall
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate attached shops worth more than Rs 13 crore in Pune's SGS Mall in the Punjab and Maharashtra Cooperative (PMC) Bank loan fraud-linked money laundering case.

news.title: Calcutta HC asks KMC to seal 10 buildings by 2 pm today
news.para: A division bench of Chief Justice T S Sivagnanam and Justice Hiranmay Bhattacharyya issued the directive on Friday while hearing a petition complaining that the “illegal constructions” were made on thika tenancy land.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh Housing Board slashes cost of flats up to 42% in Ghaziabad
news.para: These flats were originally available in a range of Rs 69.4 lakh to Rs 1.1 crore. The move was taken as few homebuyers have opted for the flats built by the board in the last ten years.

news.title: Greater Noida: Golf Links 1 society residents stage protest over lack of maintenance
news.para: The GNIDA said they will provide all municipal amenities such as sewer, streetlights, roads, parks, sanitation, etc., like sectors such as alfa, beta, gamma, etc., after the maintenance takeover.

news.title: Birla Group enters paints business with Rs 10,000 crore investment plan
news.para: Aditya Birla Group is investing in Birla Opus, its paints venture, with the aim to disrupt the industry and become the number two player. They plan to achieve a revenue of Rs 10,000 crore and cover the entire country by FY25.

news.title: Suhana Khan buys about 1.8 acres land parcel in Alibaug
news.para: Actress Suhana Khan, daughter of Bollywood icon Shahrukh Khan, has purchased a property in Alibaug, a prestigious beachfront area popular among Mumbai's affluent, for over Rs 10 crore, inclusive of stamp duty charges.

news.title: Germany: Allianz's property portfolio dips 6% on revaluations & sales
news.para: Investors are closely watching to what extent financial institutions, funds and other property owners are revising the values of their holdings or selling amid the market declines.

news.title: Housing starts in Sweden fall 49% in 2023
news.para: The Statistics Office said around 29,350 new apartments were started in the year against 57,033 in 2022.

news.title: Bhopal: Over 109 homes demolished on day 2 of eviction drive in Bhadbhada
news.para: The move to demolish structures within 50 metres of the green belt is in compliance with the orders given by the National Green Tribunal (NGT).

news.title: Gurugram civic body seals illegal seven-storey building in Jharsa
news.para: The building has been constructed on a 300 sqyard plot in Jharsa. The owner also didn’t get the building plan approved by the corporation. MCG served a show-cause notice to the owner on Jan 23, 2023 and sealed the building on Monday.

news.title: Andhra CM to distribute registered deeds of house-sites to women in Ongole
news.para: Chief Minister Jagan Mohan Reddy will distribute registered conveyance deeds of house sites to 20,000 poor women in Ongole, granting them full rights over the sites.

news.title: Patna Civic body extends property tax deadline till February 29
news.para: If they continue to default even after February 29, their buildings and houses will specially be marked during the campaign between March 1 and 5 for further action amounting to levy of hefty fines and attachment of property.

news.title: ED searches Hirandandani premises as part of FEMA probe
news.para: ​The probe pertains to alleged contravention of the Foreign Exchange Management Act (FEMA), the sources said.

news.title: Nashik civic body issues notices to 10,000 property tax defaulters
news.para: The civic body has given the defaulters a 15-day window to clear their dues, failing to which action to confiscate the properties will be initiated.

news.title: Sebi orders attachment of bank, demat accounts of DHFL's ex-promoters in disclosure violation case
news.para: ​ Markets regulator Sebi has ordered the attachment of bank accounts as well as shares and mutual fund holdings of Dheeraj Wadhawan and Kapil Wadhawan, the former promoters of Dewan Housing Finance Corp Ltd (DHFL), to recover dues totalling over Rs 22 lakh.
